            \t   <change when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages</change>\n            \t<change when=\"2020-11-20\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova added EDCS numbers</change>\n\t\t<change when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography</change>\n\t    <change when=\"2020-12-17\" who=\"#system\">Updated Zenodo DOI</change>\n            \t<change when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references</change>\n\t</listChange>\n        </revisionDesc>\n    </teiHeader>\n    <facsimile>\n        <surface type=\"front\">\n            <graphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic000964_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                <desc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana</desc>\n            </graphic>\n            <graphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic000964.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                <desc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana</desc>\n            </graphic>\n         </surface>\n    </facsimile>\n    <text>\n        <body><!-- two unchecked imported texts from PHI, revision required against Prag autopsy\n            <div type=\"edition\" xml:space=\"preserve\" subtype=\"PHI\" n=\"PHI140842\">\n                <ab>\n                    <lb n=\"1\"/>\n                    ἅπασα γέα καὶ πλατοὶς ἀὴρ\n                    <lb n=\"2\"/> \n               <expan>\n                        <abbr>γεν</abbr>\n                        <ex>ν</ex>\n                        <abbr>ᾷ</abbr>\n                    </expan> σοι, Θάνατε\n                    <lb n=\"3\"/>\n                    ἐξαπίνης μου τὸ βρέφος ἥρπασε<supplied reason=\"lost\">ς· ἦ</supplied>\n                    <lb n=\"4\"/>\n                    τίς ἀνάνκη; | εἰ γὰρ ἐγήρα, οὐχεὶ σὸν <supplied reason=\"lost\">ἦν</supplied>\n                    <lb n=\"5\"/>☧ ἐγενήθη ὁ κύρις Ἀγάθων <expan>\n                        <abbr>πρ</abbr>\n                        <ex>ὸ</ex>\n                    </expan> ιεʹ ☧\n                    <lb n=\"6\"/>\n                    καλανδῶν Νοενβρίων ἡμέρᾳ Κρό<supplied reason=\"lost\">νου</supplied>\n                    <lb n=\"7\"/>\n                        <expan>\n                        <abbr>ἔζη</abbr>\n                        <ex>σε</ex>\n                        </expan>\n                    <expan>\n                        <abbr>μῆ</abbr>\n                        <ex>νας</ex>\n                    </expan> ∙ ιαʹ<certainty match=\"preceding-sibling::node()\" locus=\"value\"/> ∙ ἀπέθανε <expan>\n                        <abbr>πρ</abbr>\n                        <ex>ὸ</ex>\n                    </expan> ∙ ιʹ ∙ καλανδῶν Σεπτενβρ<supplied reason=\"lost\">ίων</supplied>\n                    <lb n=\"8\"/>\n                     ἡμέρᾳ Ἡλίου <expan>\n                        <abbr>κυρια</abbr>\n                        <ex>κῇ</ex>\n                    </expan>. ἀγαθὴ εἰρήνη <surplus>ν</surplus> ἀγα<supplied reason=\"lost\">θοῖς</supplied>\n                </ab>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"edition\" xml:space=\"preserve\" subtype=\"PHI\" n=\"PHI316256\">\n                <ab>\n                    <lb n=\"1\"/>\n                    ἅπασα γε͂α καὶ πλατοὶς ἀὴρ\n                    <lb n=\"2\"/>\n                    γενᾷ σοι θάνατε·\n                    <lb n=\"3\"/>\n                    ἐξαπίνης μου τὸ βρέφος ἥρπασε<supplied reason=\"lost\">ς· ἦ</supplied>\n                    <lb n=\"4\"/>\n                    τίς ἀνάνκη; εἰ γὰρ ἐγήρα, οὐχεί σον <supplied reason=\"lost\">ἦν</supplied>\n                    <lb n=\"5\"/>\n                    ☧ ἐγενήθη ὁ κύρις Ἀγάθων <expan>\n                        <abbr>πρ</abbr>\n                        <ex>ὸ</ex>\n                    </expan> ιεʹ ☧\n                    <lb n=\"6\"/>\n                    καλανδῶν Νοενβρίων ἡμέρᾳ Κρό<supplied reason=\"lost\">νου</supplied>\n                    <lb n=\"7\"/>\n                    <expan>\n                        <abbr>ἔζη</abbr>\n                        <ex>σεν</ex>\n                    </expan>\n                    <expan>\n                        <abbr>μῆ</abbr>\n                        <ex>νας</ex>\n                    </expan> ∙ι∙ʹ, ἀπέθανε <expan>\n                        <abbr>πρ</abbr>\n                        <ex>ὸ</ex>\n                    </expan> ∙ι∙<gap reason=\"lost\"/>ʹ καλανδῶν Σεπτενβρί<supplied reason=\"lost\">ων</supplied>\n                    <lb n=\"8\"/>\n                    ἡμέρᾳ Ἡλίου· κυρία Ἀγάθη εἰρήνην Ἀγά<supplied reason=\"lost\">θωνι</supplied>\n                </ab>\n              </div>  -->\n            <div type=\"edition\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#JP\"><!-- needs encoding-->\n                <ab><lb n=\"1\"/>Ἅπασα γε̑α καὶ πλατοὶς ἀὴρ\n                    <lb n=\"2\"/>γενᾷ σοι θάνατε\n                    <lb n=\"3\"/>ἐξαπίνης μου τὸ βρέφος ἥρπασε[ς ἦ]\n                    <lb n=\"4\"/>τίς ἀνάκη εἰ γὰρ ἐγήρα, οὐχεί σον [ἦν]\n                    <lb n=\"5\"/>((chrismon)) ἐγενήθη ὁ κύρις Ἀγάθων π͡ρ(ὸ) ιε’ ((chrismon))\n                    <lb n=\"6\"/>καλανδῶν Νοενβρίων ἡμέρᾳ Κρό[νου]\n                    <lb n=\"7\"/>ἔζη(σεν) μ͡ῆ(νας) ·ι’· ἀπέθανε π͡ρ(ὸ) · ι’·[-?] καλανδῶν Σεπτενβρ[ίων]\n                    <lb n=\"8\"/>ἡμέρᾳ Ἡλίου κυρία Ἀγάθη εἰρήνην Ἀγά[θωνι]\n                </ab>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"apparatus\">\n                <p><!--external apparatus criticus (if applicable)--></p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                <p>All the earth and the air in its wide expanses begets you, o Death. On a sudden, you snatched away my\n                    babe – or was there some necessity, for if he had grown old, would he not still have been yours?\n                    Master Agathon was born the 15th day before the Kalends of November (= 18th October), on the day of\n                    Kronos; he lived 11 months; he died the tenth day before the Kalends of September (= 23rd August),\n                    on the day of the Sun. Lady Agatha, (grant) peace for Agathon!</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"it\" resp=\"#SA\">\n                <p>Tutta la terra e il vasto etere generano per te, o Morte. All'improvviso mi hai strappato via il\n                    bambino, che necessità c’era? Infatti se fosse invecchiato, non sarebbe stato pur sempre tuo? Il\n                    signore Agathon nacque quindici giorni prima delle calende di novembre (= 18 Ottobre) nel giorno di\n                    Kronos. Visse undici mesi; morì dieci giorni prima delle calende di settembre (= 23 agosto) nel\n                    giorno del Sole. Signora Agatha, (conceda) la pace a Agathon.</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"commentary\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->\n                    <!--Ref. to Sunday as Hemera Heliou is unusual - cf. IG 14.0235; 0165. Agathon is the deceased; Note birthday is recorded as well as death and age, which is unique in Gr. epig. in Sic, rare generally; parallel in Agnello, Sill. n.85, the Latin epitaph of Iulia Florentina; extensive discussion by Feissel. He thinks this also has ref to St.Agatha, the martyr of Catania; cf. IGPalermo pp.142-3 no.112.-->\n                    The first four lines are in verse, and express ideas typical in pagan funerary inscriptions; the\n                    chi-rho symbols and the latter part of the text show that this is clearly a Christian epitaph. It is\n                    rare to mention the date of birth, especially in Greek Christian texts, and most parallels are for\n                    infants, as here. The closest parallel is the famous epitaph of Julia Florentina from Catania (now\n                    in the Louvre, Paris: Ma2994), an infant who was buried before the shrine of the martyrs, perhaps\n                    including St. Agatha. The significance of the final line of the text is debated, but it appears to\n                    be a prayer to Saint Agatha, in which case this provides the earliest contemporary evidence for the\n                    cult of St. Agatha at Catania, of similar date to that for St. Lucia at Siracusa in the epitaph for\n                    Euskia (Museo Archeologico Regionale Paolo Orsi, inv.14600).</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"bibliography\">\n                <listBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    <bibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"IG\">\n                        <citedRange>\n                            <ref target=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\">14.0525</ref>\n                        </citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"SEG\">\n                        <citedRange>31.0830</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"BE\">\n                        <citedRange>1982.0506</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/77P5MNIR\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"IMusCatania\">\n                        <citedRange>174</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/2EUC82DH\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"CIG\">\n                        <citedRange>4.9475</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HTUDQBXS\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001252\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001252</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl>\n                        <author>Agnello</author>\n                        <date>1953</date>\n                        <citedRange>no.106</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/D9BZFDDR\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"IGCVO\">\n                        <citedRange>1042</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/9CT5ZWIK\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl>\n                        <author>Feissel</author>\n                        <date>1981</date>\n                        <citedRange>494 no.xv</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/AWUTDEHF\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002010\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002010</ref></bibl>\n                </listBibl>\n\t   <listBibl type=\"discussion\"><bibl/></listBibl>\n            </div>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>\n",
